WEBVTT

00:01.130 --> 00:03.220
I agree with the Pink Ladies.

00:03.420 --> 00:04.440
<i>We can't trust Susan.</i>

00:04.640 --> 00:06.180
She's Susan.

00:06.380 --> 00:09.360
- Principal says, the kids
can have rock and roll.

00:09.560 --> 00:11.320
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

00:11.520 --> 00:13.100
- It doesn't hurt
to have the Aldridge name

00:13.300 --> 00:15.190
out there right before
I announce my campaign.

00:15.390 --> 00:16.760
- Sorry, but we won't be
able to host

00:16.960 --> 00:17.800
any of you this evening.

00:18.000 --> 00:19.280
How convenient.

00:20.450 --> 00:22.110
We don't need a gym.

00:22.310 --> 00:24.200
Party at Frosty's.

00:24.400 --> 00:26.030
Don't break anything.

00:26.230 --> 00:27.030
What about Buddy?

00:27.230 --> 00:28.420
What about him?

00:28.620 --> 00:29.900
all: ♪ Rock and roll

00:30.100 --> 00:31.300
<i>We did it.</i>

00:31.500 --> 00:32.690
<i>It's the party</i>
<i>we always wanted.</i>

00:32.890 --> 00:34.770
<i>♪ </i>

00:36.120 --> 00:37.650
- If you were a real man,
you'd like it.

00:37.850 --> 00:39.130
<i>- You tried to make</i>
<i>everyone think</i>

00:39.330 --> 00:41.440
<i>that Jane is easy,</i>
<i>when you're the one who</i>

00:41.640 --> 00:44.090
put out for Buddy Aldridge.

00:44.290 --> 00:47.360
- My dad and Nicholson
rigged the votes.

00:47.560 --> 00:49.140
Jane.
Jane, please.

00:49.340 --> 00:50.490
Let me explain.
Jane, please.

00:50.690 --> 00:51.930
- Just leave her alone.
- Out of my way.

00:52.130 --> 00:53.710
Richie. Richie!

00:53.910 --> 00:55.540
[shrieks]

00:55.740 --> 00:56.930
<i>This is all your fault.</i>

00:57.130 --> 00:58.890
<i> If you would just pick a side,</i>

00:59.090 --> 01:00.330
- pick a boy.
- Come on. Let's cool it.

01:00.520 --> 01:01.540
- Pink Ladies have
to stick together.

01:01.740 --> 01:02.760
Yeah.

01:02.960 --> 01:04.020
Maybe I'm done
being a Pink Lady.

01:04.220 --> 01:06.590
<i>♪ </i>

01:06.790 --> 01:08.800
<i>- ♪ It's cursing you,</i>
<i>it's crushing me ♪</i>

01:12.330 --> 01:14.860
<i>[Andy Russell's "What a</i>
<i>Diff'rence a Day Made"]</i>

01:15.060 --> 01:16.380
<i>♪ </i>

01:16.580 --> 01:22.170
<i>- ♪ What a difference</i>
<i>a day made ♪</i>

01:22.370 --> 01:25.180
<i>♪ 24 little hours </i>

01:25.380 --> 01:26.790
[bell chimes]

01:26.990 --> 01:28.090
<i>- [on radio] Tonight,</i>
<i>Rydell is still reeling</i>

01:28.290 --> 01:29.220
<i>from Saturday night's</i>
<i>rock 'n' roll riot.</i>

01:29.420 --> 01:30.750
<i>The trouble started when</i>

01:30.950 --> 01:32.010
<i>some Rydell High juvenile</i>
<i>delinquents...</i>

01:32.210 --> 01:33.530
- She's been calling
her friends all weekend.

01:33.730 --> 01:35.660
None of them will answer.

01:35.860 --> 01:37.010
<i>- [on radio] ...but this time</i>
<i>with rock 'n' roll</i>

01:37.210 --> 01:38.450
<i>and free-flowing liquor.</i>

01:38.650 --> 01:40.150
<i>The bash quickly turned into</i>
<i>a violent brawl</i>

01:40.350 --> 01:42.630
<i>when two rival gangs used</i>
<i>the Frosty Palace as the--</i>

01:42.830 --> 01:43.930
[radio switches off]

01:44.130 --> 01:45.240
[bell chimes]

01:45.440 --> 01:46.550
Nancy, your friends are here.

01:46.740 --> 01:47.930
Oh.

01:49.060 --> 01:50.550
Ooh.

01:50.750 --> 01:52.380
- Nancy, we broke up
with Bill and Roy.

01:52.580 --> 01:54.770
When the cops came, they ran
off and left us for dead.

01:54.970 --> 01:56.290
- And they've forgotten
all our anniversaries--

01:56.490 --> 01:57.730
one and two month.

01:57.930 --> 01:59.460
- We should have
listened to you.

02:00.850 --> 02:02.120
We miss you.

02:03.510 --> 02:06.000
Have a milkshake with us?

02:06.200 --> 02:08.740
<i>[The Platters'</i>
<i>"The Great Pretender"]</i>

02:08.940 --> 02:11.350
I guess so.

02:11.550 --> 02:16.440
<i>- ♪ Oh, yes,</i>
<i>I'm the great pretender ♪</i>

02:16.640 --> 02:18.400
[echoing voices and laughter]

02:18.600 --> 02:22.450
<i>♪ Pretending that</i>
<i>I'm doing well ♪</i>

02:22.650 --> 02:24.370
<i>♪ </i>

02:24.570 --> 02:30.420
<i>♪ My need is such,</i>
<i>I pretend too much ♪</i>

02:30.610 --> 02:33.330
<i>♪ I'm lonely,</i>
<i>but no one... ♪</i>

02:33.530 --> 02:35.500
[screams]

02:37.200 --> 02:39.990
Sorry, but I already have
three best friends,

02:40.190 --> 02:42.510
and they would never dump me
for drips like Ralph and Boy.

02:42.710 --> 02:44.120
It's Bill and Roy.

02:44.320 --> 02:45.460
- Didn't the Pink Ladies
break up?

02:48.550 --> 02:49.870
- We're about to get
back together.

02:50.070 --> 02:52.130
[thunder rumbles]

02:52.330 --> 02:56.000
My condolences
on Phil and Troy.

02:57.520 --> 02:59.530
<i>♪ I'm wearing my heart </i>

02:59.730 --> 03:01.710
- You have to finish
your shift.

03:01.910 --> 03:04.140
- I know.
Just let me do this.

03:04.340 --> 03:07.630
<i>♪ Pretending that you're </i>

03:07.830 --> 03:11.240
<i>♪ Still around </i>

03:11.440 --> 03:14.200
<i>[dramatic brassy music]</i>

03:14.400 --> 03:21.240
<i>♪ </i>

03:26.330 --> 03:29.250
[thunder rumbles]

03:31.730 --> 03:34.520
- Miss McGee, if this is about
the dance, I can explain.

03:34.720 --> 03:37.120
- I didn't call you here
to talk about the dance.

03:41.780 --> 03:43.790
Congratulations.

03:43.990 --> 03:46.100
You are now officially
Rydell High's

03:46.300 --> 03:48.930
first girl president.

03:49.130 --> 03:50.710
- I--I--I don't understand.

03:50.910 --> 03:52.450
- Details about the election
have come to light,

03:52.650 --> 03:53.980
and we think it's
only fair that you

03:54.180 --> 03:56.110
take your rightful position.

03:56.310 --> 03:59.370
Principal Nicholson has asked
me to pass on his apologies,

03:59.570 --> 04:01.800
and he hopes there are
"No hard feelings, sweetheart."

04:03.930 --> 04:06.210
Jane, this is
a big responsibility--

04:06.410 --> 04:08.300
especially now.

04:08.500 --> 04:10.860
I hope you'll use
this gavel wisely.

04:11.060 --> 04:13.120
[thunder rumbling]

04:31.740 --> 04:33.570
He spent two nights in jail.

04:36.010 --> 04:37.670
Is he okay?

04:37.870 --> 04:38.760
Are they going
to press charges?

04:38.960 --> 04:40.550
No.

04:40.740 --> 04:42.020
That doesn't matter.

04:42.220 --> 04:45.290
They're both in there
getting expelled.

04:45.490 --> 04:47.380
And my parents are sending
Richie off to military school.

04:47.580 --> 04:48.420
What?

04:48.620 --> 04:49.680
Where?

04:49.880 --> 04:51.160
Ohio, I don't know.

04:51.360 --> 04:52.730
It's just all
happening so fast.

04:52.930 --> 04:54.040
- Oh, Olivia--

04:54.240 --> 04:55.080
No!

04:55.280 --> 04:58.080
<i>[somber music]</i>

04:58.280 --> 04:59.430
<i>♪ </i>

04:59.630 --> 05:01.600
I see you got what you wanted.

05:03.170 --> 05:04.570
Congratulations.

05:04.770 --> 05:06.270
This is ridiculous!

05:06.470 --> 05:08.390
Good luck running for
superintendent without me.

05:10.390 --> 05:12.310
Lose my number.

05:15.220 --> 05:17.360
Buddy, I'm so sorry.

05:19.100 --> 05:20.020
Come on.

05:20.220 --> 05:27.060
<i>♪ </i>

05:41.600 --> 05:44.560
- I can't believe it's
my last day at Rydell.

05:46.380 --> 05:48.530
So where am I headed next, huh?

05:48.730 --> 05:51.010
Washington High?

05:51.210 --> 05:55.350
- I've already put a call into
Clifton Day, my alma mater.

05:56.920 --> 05:59.320
That's in Connecticut.

05:59.520 --> 06:01.320
- Buddy, after everything
that's happened,

06:01.520 --> 06:04.280
it'll be good for you to
get out of town for a while.

06:04.480 --> 06:06.670
You come back after graduation,
and everyone will have

06:06.870 --> 06:09.020
forgotten all about
this hullabaloo.

06:09.220 --> 06:10.590
- I thought you said you
hated that place, Dad.

06:10.790 --> 06:12.200
- Well, for better
or for worse, Buddy,

06:12.400 --> 06:13.860
it made me the man I am today.

06:14.060 --> 06:16.210
It's the best thing for you.

06:16.410 --> 06:19.500
- Or is it the best thing
for you and your campaign?

06:21.110 --> 06:22.640
- Now, son--

06:30.730 --> 06:33.660
"Cynthia, had to go.

06:33.860 --> 06:35.270
"Won't be needing this
anymore, but I think it

06:35.470 --> 06:37.310
"looked better on you anyway.

06:37.510 --> 06:38.750
Richie."

06:38.950 --> 06:41.710
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

06:41.910 --> 06:48.750
<i>♪ </i>

06:50.970 --> 06:52.410
Whew.

06:54.580 --> 06:57.160
- Remember, you don't want your
jelly roll to be too loose,

06:57.360 --> 06:59.290
or no one will want your treat.

06:59.490 --> 07:00.820
Too late for some of us.

07:01.020 --> 07:02.300
[blows raspberry]

07:02.500 --> 07:03.780
It's just a joke.

07:03.970 --> 07:05.650
[giggling]

07:05.850 --> 07:08.130
- Ms. Adcock, my doctor
doesn't want me to do any tasks

07:08.330 --> 07:09.520
that require depth perception.

07:09.720 --> 07:11.040
Can I be excused?

07:11.240 --> 07:13.440
Oh, fine.

07:13.640 --> 07:15.700
You're on laundry duty.

07:15.900 --> 07:17.610
[giggling]

07:26.570 --> 07:28.760
- Olivia, can you help Jane
with her sewing machine?

07:28.960 --> 07:32.490
I just don't know how
to work this crazy thing.

07:34.580 --> 07:36.190
Terrible try, Nancy.

07:39.020 --> 07:41.160
Thanks, Nancy.

07:41.360 --> 07:43.080
I don't think
there's any point.

07:43.270 --> 07:45.380
Cynthia, you're tardy.

07:45.580 --> 07:47.120
<i>[rhythmic rock music]</i>

07:47.320 --> 07:48.820
Sorry.

07:49.020 --> 07:50.740
I had better things to do.

07:50.930 --> 07:56.910
<i>♪ </i>

07:58.430 --> 08:00.660
- What in Balenciaga's name
are you wearing?

08:00.860 --> 08:02.090
Richie left me his jacket.

08:02.290 --> 08:03.400
Well, take it off.

08:03.600 --> 08:04.970
You already have a gang.

08:05.170 --> 08:06.400
We have to be the ones
to keep it together

08:06.600 --> 08:07.880
while Grumpy and Dopey
are fighting.

08:08.080 --> 08:10.410
- Nancy, read the writing
on the wall.

08:10.610 --> 08:11.670
Richie's getting
sent away soon.

08:11.870 --> 08:13.930
Olivia blames Jane.

08:14.130 --> 08:15.660
I don't think we come
back from that.

08:19.410 --> 08:22.200
Well, even if we lost Olivia,

08:22.400 --> 08:24.290
the rest of us could still
be Pink Ladies.

08:24.490 --> 08:26.500
[school bell rings]

08:30.460 --> 08:32.070
I don't know.

08:33.160 --> 08:36.300
I mean, now that it's all over,
it seems kind of crazy.

08:36.500 --> 08:38.000
Me?

08:38.200 --> 08:39.600
A Pink Lady?

08:41.520 --> 08:43.080
We can still pal around,
though.

08:44.740 --> 08:47.010
[thunder rumbles]

08:47.210 --> 08:48.790
Military school?

08:48.990 --> 08:50.010
Damn.

08:50.210 --> 08:51.360
He could have said goodbye.

08:51.560 --> 08:52.670
He's not gone yet.

08:52.870 --> 08:53.890
We'll sneak him out tonight
and give him

08:54.080 --> 08:56.410
one last hurrah before he goes.

08:56.610 --> 08:58.450
- The Birds aren't ever
going to be the same.

09:00.620 --> 09:01.590
Hey.

09:01.790 --> 09:02.630
Oof!

09:02.830 --> 09:04.030
Yeah, just let him go.

09:04.230 --> 09:04.980
It's not going to help.

09:05.180 --> 09:06.070
Oh.

09:06.270 --> 09:07.200
Sorry about Richie, guys.

09:07.400 --> 09:09.200
Thanks, man.

09:09.400 --> 09:10.810
Hiya, fellas.

09:15.940 --> 09:17.470
Richie said he
wanted me to have it,

09:17.670 --> 09:19.900
and since my other
gang fell apart...

09:24.080 --> 09:25.660
I'm sorry.

09:25.860 --> 09:29.310
You can't wear that, because
that's what we're wearing.

09:29.510 --> 09:31.230
And if you're wearing
what we're wearing...

09:31.430 --> 09:33.930
[thunder rumbles]

09:34.120 --> 09:36.280
What will the society pages
say?

09:36.470 --> 09:37.930
[laughter]

09:38.130 --> 09:40.110
- They'll say I wear it
better than your ugly mugs.

09:40.300 --> 09:41.890
Welcome to the Birds!

09:42.090 --> 09:43.590
- We should have given you
one of these a long time ago.

09:43.790 --> 09:45.590
I'm sorry you had
to get it like this.

09:45.790 --> 09:46.620
Take that off.

09:48.410 --> 09:49.810
Down, boy.

09:50.010 --> 09:51.600
Richie gave it to her.
It's all copacetic.

09:51.790 --> 09:52.860
I don't care.

09:53.060 --> 09:54.730
I don't want her in the gang.

09:54.930 --> 09:55.860
I mean it.

09:56.060 --> 09:57.300
If she's in, I'm out.

09:57.500 --> 09:59.690
<i>[somber music]</i>

09:59.890 --> 10:01.130
- Hey!
Shy Guy!

10:01.330 --> 10:02.560
Shy Guy! Hey!

10:02.760 --> 10:04.030
Shy Guy.

10:05.300 --> 10:06.570
Shy Guy!

10:06.770 --> 10:08.130
Hey!

10:08.330 --> 10:10.440
- Connecticut.
That's far.

10:10.640 --> 10:11.880
- Hey, if you were going
to go out, at least

10:12.080 --> 10:13.740
you did it swinging, huh?

10:16.130 --> 10:17.450
You're a legend.

10:17.650 --> 10:18.540
- We're going to call
you every weekend.

10:18.730 --> 10:20.010
And I'll write you every day.

10:20.210 --> 10:21.320
I bet.

10:21.520 --> 10:23.370
[giggling]

10:23.570 --> 10:25.410
- I don't know what
I'm doing here.

10:25.610 --> 10:27.020
I don't need any of this stuff.

10:27.220 --> 10:28.370
- Can I have your
Mickey Mantle?

10:28.570 --> 10:29.840
- Wally.
- What?

10:31.230 --> 10:32.590
Yeah.

10:32.790 --> 10:34.730
Why don't you just
raid the whole thing?

10:34.920 --> 10:36.470
Let's be honest, huh?

10:36.670 --> 10:38.900
Once I'm gone, I'll be gone.

10:39.100 --> 10:41.510
So why don't we just say
goodbye and not drag this out?

10:41.710 --> 10:43.120
[locker shuts]

10:43.320 --> 10:44.470
Here.

10:44.670 --> 10:45.860
Buddy.

10:47.770 --> 10:49.220
Military school?

10:49.420 --> 10:50.960
Those places are awful.

10:51.160 --> 10:52.480
- [crying] They think it's
going to straighten him out,

10:52.680 --> 10:53.950
but it's just
going to crush him.

10:57.740 --> 11:01.140
Thank you for being there
for me the other night,

11:01.340 --> 11:04.490
and not taking advantage
of the situation.

11:04.690 --> 11:05.750
I wouldn't dream of it.

11:07.360 --> 11:10.020
I know you're a
good Catholic girl.

11:10.220 --> 11:12.240
- That's not what everyone
at this school thinks.

11:12.440 --> 11:14.290
Well, they don't know you.

11:14.490 --> 11:15.550
I do.

11:15.750 --> 11:18.200
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

11:18.400 --> 11:22.860
<i>♪ </i>

11:23.060 --> 11:25.380
This isn't working.

11:25.580 --> 11:27.260
- A-am I doing something wrong?

11:27.460 --> 11:28.430
Nope.

11:28.630 --> 11:29.780
Solid 7 out of 10, like always.

11:29.980 --> 11:30.960
Thank you.

11:31.150 --> 11:32.480
I don't get it.

11:32.680 --> 11:34.740
Usually kissing helps
tame the hormones that

11:34.940 --> 11:37.220
cloud my visionary brain,
but I still

11:37.420 --> 11:39.750
don't know how to get my
friends to talk to each other.

11:39.950 --> 11:41.620
- Maybe they'll come around.
- No.

11:41.820 --> 11:44.360
I have had friends
drift away before.

11:44.560 --> 11:46.360
The longer this goes on,
the less likely it is

11:46.560 --> 11:48.150
the Pink Ladies will
get back together.

11:48.350 --> 11:50.450
I have to nip this
in the bud today.

11:50.650 --> 11:53.980
- Hey, you and I are the two
smartest people in the school.

11:54.180 --> 11:55.150
Agreed.

11:55.350 --> 11:56.680
We can figure this out.

11:56.880 --> 11:57.980
[school bell rings]

11:58.180 --> 11:59.160
Last period.

11:59.360 --> 12:00.720
We have to think fast.

12:03.760 --> 12:06.560
Oh, that's terrible.

12:06.760 --> 12:08.120
Yes, I understand.

12:08.320 --> 12:10.560
Yes, thank you very much.

12:10.760 --> 12:13.950
The unprecedented rain has
caused some serious mudslides

12:14.150 --> 12:15.700
and flooding in town.

12:15.900 --> 12:18.050
The superintendent wants us
to keep the children here

12:18.250 --> 12:19.480
for everyone's safety.

12:19.680 --> 12:21.350
But did he ask about me?

12:21.550 --> 12:22.570
Who?

12:22.770 --> 12:24.530
Superintendent Fletcher.

12:24.730 --> 12:25.710
No.

12:25.910 --> 12:26.970
[clears throat] Okay.

12:27.170 --> 12:28.400
Hmm.

12:28.600 --> 12:30.840
Wait, you're saying
we'll be stuck here

12:31.040 --> 12:32.150
with all these kids?

12:32.350 --> 12:33.280
Until when?

12:33.480 --> 12:35.020
Until the storm is over.

12:35.220 --> 12:36.930
But I have a plan.

12:37.130 --> 12:39.500
We'll keep everyone in their
homerooms with their teachers.

12:39.700 --> 12:41.160
Everyone will require
a hall pass to--

12:41.360 --> 12:42.630
[door shuts]

12:46.410 --> 12:47.730
"Great plan, McGee.

12:47.930 --> 12:49.160
See you've got it
under control."

12:49.360 --> 12:50.380
Yes, I do.

12:50.580 --> 12:51.820
Thank you, Principal Nicholson!

12:52.020 --> 12:53.690
"I'm going to make you
superintendent

12:53.890 --> 12:55.650
of all the schools
in the world."

12:55.850 --> 12:58.740
Thank you, Principal Nicholson,
because I work so hard!

12:58.940 --> 12:59.740
[door slams]

12:59.940 --> 13:02.000
[thunder cracks]

13:02.200 --> 13:05.480
This reminds me of old times,

13:05.680 --> 13:07.490
before everything,

13:07.690 --> 13:09.750
talking about books we love,

13:09.950 --> 13:12.930
talking about books you love
and I secretly hated,

13:13.130 --> 13:14.540
but lied to you about.

13:14.740 --> 13:15.800
What?

13:16.000 --> 13:18.190
What books did you hate?

13:18.390 --> 13:21.460
- "Walden," by Henry David
Thor-eau-yourself-

13:21.660 --> 13:22.810
into-that-pond-already.

13:23.010 --> 13:24.980
- Oh, come on!
That's a classic.

13:25.180 --> 13:26.680
- Yeah, if you like books
about hermits who won't

13:26.880 --> 13:29.600
shut up about their...
bean fields.

13:29.790 --> 13:32.770
Ooh! Wow.

13:32.970 --> 13:35.990
You must really have liked me.

13:36.190 --> 13:38.520
<i>♪ </i>

13:38.720 --> 13:40.820
I do really like you.

13:41.020 --> 13:42.780
<i>[tender music]</i>

13:42.980 --> 13:44.690
[knocking at door]

13:50.740 --> 13:52.010
- Here's my latest article,
Mr. Daniels.

13:52.210 --> 13:54.790
Oh, thanks.

13:54.990 --> 13:56.360
Thanks, Virginia.

13:56.560 --> 13:58.450
- Okay.
- All right.

13:58.650 --> 13:59.790
Bye.

14:05.930 --> 14:07.320
All clear.

14:09.410 --> 14:11.510
- That feels like
old times too.

14:11.710 --> 14:13.380
I know.

14:13.580 --> 14:15.290
I hate sneaking around.

