Uh, Nancy told me
to give this to you.

31:27.220 --> 31:28.980
Maybe this could wait?

31:29.180 --> 31:31.280
- She's crying
in the girls' room.

31:31.480 --> 31:33.020
She won't talk to me.

31:36.320 --> 31:38.240
I'll be back.

31:42.810 --> 31:44.520
What'd I do?

31:44.710 --> 31:45.860
[toilet flushes]

31:46.060 --> 31:47.170
Must have been a doozy.

31:47.370 --> 31:49.390
- Jeez, how do you
keep finding me?

31:49.590 --> 31:50.960
The school's not that big.

31:51.160 --> 31:52.960
There's only so many places
you can hide.

31:53.160 --> 31:54.220
Since we're stuck
here together,

31:54.420 --> 31:55.870
you may as well talk to me.

31:56.070 --> 31:58.010
- I'm considering taking
my chances with the storm.

31:58.210 --> 31:59.310
- Now that you're
speaking to me,

31:59.510 --> 32:00.440
you want to tell
me why you've got

32:00.640 --> 32:02.880
your undies in such a twist?

32:03.080 --> 32:04.580
- You can't pretend
what happened at the dance

32:04.780 --> 32:06.060
didn't happen.

32:06.260 --> 32:07.840
That's what this is about?

32:08.040 --> 32:09.360
A bad date?

32:12.010 --> 32:13.370
You're going to throw
away a friendship

32:13.570 --> 32:15.240
we've had since the
fourth grade over that?

32:15.440 --> 32:16.500
Maybe.

32:16.700 --> 32:17.680
Jeez!

32:17.880 --> 32:20.200
Who knew you were so sensitive?

32:20.400 --> 32:23.680
I'm not sensitive.

32:23.880 --> 32:25.560
You said I wasn't a real man.

32:25.760 --> 32:27.120
- I didn't mean that. I--

32:27.320 --> 32:28.730
- You can't say things like
that, even if that's what

32:28.930 --> 32:30.040
- everybody thinks about me.
- No one thinks that.

32:30.240 --> 32:31.560
Yes, they do!

32:31.760 --> 32:33.350
I'm so shy, nobody even
remembers my real name.

32:33.550 --> 32:36.380
I don't need you throwing
it in my face too.

32:38.170 --> 32:40.090
Cynthia!

32:40.290 --> 32:41.560
You've got to see this.

32:42.960 --> 32:44.350
It's from Nancy.

32:53.750 --> 32:55.790
[knocking]

32:58.540 --> 32:59.850
Ugh.

33:00.050 --> 33:01.330
I'm very busy.

33:01.530 --> 33:04.030
- I have school business--
from the class president.

33:04.230 --> 33:06.250
Oh.

33:06.450 --> 33:08.080
- I--I'd love to talk about
how I can help you

33:08.280 --> 33:10.200
with your campaign
for superintendent.

33:13.120 --> 33:14.610
Everyone in town
thinks that you're

33:14.800 --> 33:17.430
just this ineffective
bureaucrat

33:17.630 --> 33:19.090
who can't control his students.

33:19.290 --> 33:20.740
But--but--but!

33:20.940 --> 33:23.830
You know what people respect
more than penalization?

33:24.030 --> 33:25.920
Rehabilitation.

33:26.120 --> 33:28.750
- Are you trying
to sell me a dictionary?

33:28.950 --> 33:31.010
- Instead of expelling
the boys,

33:31.210 --> 33:33.410
you should keep them at Rydell,

33:33.610 --> 33:35.190
make them clean up their acts.

33:35.390 --> 33:37.800
You'd look like a hero.

33:38.000 --> 33:39.530
A reformer.

33:45.500 --> 33:47.860
Well, that...

33:48.060 --> 33:49.070
is a dumb idea.

33:49.270 --> 33:50.860
Voters don't want a softie.

33:51.060 --> 33:52.990
They want someone who's
tough on delinquency.

33:53.190 --> 33:54.340
And that's me.

33:54.540 --> 33:55.550
- No, I--

34:00.380 --> 34:01.570
Jane!

34:01.760 --> 34:03.260
It's Nancy.

34:03.460 --> 34:04.480
She needs you right away.

34:04.680 --> 34:05.530
Nancy?

34:05.730 --> 34:06.920
[sobbing]

34:07.120 --> 34:08.310
I came as soon as I could.

34:08.510 --> 34:09.570
Will you come out now?

34:09.770 --> 34:11.010
- We're really worried
about you.

34:11.210 --> 34:12.870
- We thought you were going
to do something drastic.

34:15.480 --> 34:17.710
That's because I am.

34:17.910 --> 34:20.370
I'm taking the drastic
measure of locking us

34:20.570 --> 34:23.330
all in here until we
work out our problems.

34:23.530 --> 34:24.750
Now!

34:27.060 --> 34:28.510
Nancy, this isn't funny.

34:28.700 --> 34:29.940
- Yeah, we thought
something was really wrong.

34:30.140 --> 34:31.510
Something is really wrong.

34:31.710 --> 34:33.030
You all are letting
the Pink Ladies fall apart

34:33.230 --> 34:35.340
when we need each other
the most.

34:35.540 --> 34:37.510
Now, you two.

34:37.710 --> 34:39.030
Talk.

34:40.550 --> 34:42.080
- I'm sorry.
I need to go.

34:42.280 --> 34:43.390
I was in the middle
of something.

34:43.590 --> 34:45.830
No one is going anywhere

34:46.030 --> 34:47.650
until we are all friends again.

34:47.850 --> 34:50.660
Now, you leave me no choice.

34:50.860 --> 34:53.830
It's time for some
brutal honesty.

34:56.220 --> 34:59.060
Cynthia, you can put on
all the jackets you want.

34:59.260 --> 35:00.360
You're never going
to be a T-Bird.

35:00.560 --> 35:01.710
Hello!

35:01.910 --> 35:03.410
You're clearly not
like the others.

35:03.610 --> 35:06.530
You don't fit in anywhere,
except for with us.

35:09.540 --> 35:10.760
Damn, Nancy.

35:10.960 --> 35:12.460
And you?

35:12.660 --> 35:14.380
Without the Pink Ladies,
you'll go back to being

35:14.580 --> 35:15.860
the depressed school floozy--

35:16.060 --> 35:17.550
no brother, no friends.

35:17.750 --> 35:19.470
The only people who
will want to talk to you

35:19.670 --> 35:21.950
are the guys who
only want one thing.

35:22.150 --> 35:25.300
But when you're a Pink Lady,
we've got your back.

35:25.500 --> 35:26.870
Nancy, that's enough.

35:27.070 --> 35:29.610
- And Brainy Janey,
you think you would have

35:29.810 --> 35:31.920
won the election without us?
[snorts]

35:32.120 --> 35:34.440
We're the ones that taught you
to make a scene,

35:34.640 --> 35:36.360
break the rules,
color outside the lines.

35:36.560 --> 35:38.310
But without the Pink Ladies

35:38.510 --> 35:41.100
you're just a rule-following
goody-two-shoes

35:41.300 --> 35:44.060
who not even the Socs
want to be friends with.

35:44.260 --> 35:47.450
But with the Pink Ladies
you are--

35:47.650 --> 35:49.980
Shut up, Nancy!

35:50.180 --> 35:52.420
You're just making
things worse.

35:52.610 --> 35:54.370
And we've all got more
important things to do.

35:54.570 --> 35:56.720
It's nice to know what you
really think of us, though.

35:56.920 --> 36:01.080
- It seems like you're the only
one who needs the Pink Ladies.

36:01.280 --> 36:02.590
- Well--

36:04.770 --> 36:06.820
[grunting]

36:07.020 --> 36:08.680
Potato, it's not funny.

36:10.860 --> 36:12.170
Wait, wait! Just listen!

36:12.370 --> 36:14.300
- One, two, three--[grunts]

36:17.950 --> 36:20.310
- Just listen! I--

36:20.510 --> 36:21.390
oh!

36:23.960 --> 36:25.620
Hey, you okay?

36:25.820 --> 36:27.150
I'm fine.

36:27.350 --> 36:28.360
We'll come up with another
plan to get them back.

36:28.560 --> 36:29.840
I don't need your help.

36:30.040 --> 36:31.150
I don't need anyone.

36:31.350 --> 36:33.110
Just...

36:33.310 --> 36:34.200
bye.

36:34.400 --> 36:37.160
<i>[dramatic acoustic music]</i>

36:37.360 --> 36:41.120
<i>♪ </i>

36:41.320 --> 36:44.160
[echoing voices]

36:44.360 --> 36:50.990
<i>♪ </i>

37:04.130 --> 37:05.870
[rain pattering]

37:12.180 --> 37:14.060
- Peg, I want you to have
my lucky pencil.

37:14.260 --> 37:16.370
And Neil,

37:16.570 --> 37:17.980
this shoeshine brush
has got your name on it.

37:18.180 --> 37:19.850
Just what I always wanted.

37:20.050 --> 37:21.680
[laughs]

37:21.880 --> 37:23.540
And Wally...

37:28.980 --> 37:30.810
You've always been there
for me.

37:33.250 --> 37:34.870
Please call me in Connecticut.

37:35.060 --> 37:36.390
I'm going to need it.

37:36.590 --> 37:37.510
I will.

37:39.080 --> 37:40.650
[exhales]

37:40.850 --> 37:42.130
I'm going to miss you guys.

37:42.330 --> 37:44.780
[laughter]

37:51.610 --> 37:53.670
All right. Where's Susan?

37:53.870 --> 37:54.750
- Have you checked
under the bleachers?

37:54.950 --> 37:56.020
[giggling]

37:56.220 --> 37:58.310
Hey, that's enough.

38:04.670 --> 38:06.380
- Hey, Wally,
you want to trade with--

38:06.570 --> 38:07.810
Never in my life.

38:08.010 --> 38:08.990
- Come on, let me just
hold it for a second.

38:09.190 --> 38:10.030
You got a brush.

38:10.230 --> 38:11.370
I got Mickey Mantle.

38:13.290 --> 38:15.780
[indistinct]

38:15.980 --> 38:17.550
She spit on me.

38:23.340 --> 38:26.090
I'm sorry for the dance.

38:26.290 --> 38:29.880
I know what it feels like
to not...

38:30.080 --> 38:31.610
be like the others.

38:33.220 --> 38:35.440
Didn't mean to make
you feel that way too.

38:36.700 --> 38:40.190
- You know, I always thought
that if you liked me back,

38:40.390 --> 38:42.720
and you were my girl,

38:42.920 --> 38:44.620
I wouldn't stick out
like a sore thumb.

38:46.190 --> 38:48.500
Sorry.

38:48.700 --> 38:50.150
Just didn't feel right.

38:51.720 --> 38:53.760
Yeah. I know.

38:56.290 --> 38:58.460
Not to me either.

39:09.520 --> 39:13.010
I've been thinking lately,

39:13.210 --> 39:16.840
maybe I should stop worrying
so much about...

39:17.040 --> 39:20.230
why I feel something,

39:20.430 --> 39:23.830
and...just feel it.

39:33.150 --> 39:36.160
- You can be a T-Bird
if you want.

39:36.360 --> 39:37.940
Hmm.

39:38.140 --> 39:39.990
Funny.

39:40.190 --> 39:43.550
After all that,
it just doesn't feel right.

39:44.900 --> 39:46.650
But thanks--

39:46.850 --> 39:48.420
Edward.

39:56.690 --> 39:58.490
[bell dings]
[line ringing]

39:58.690 --> 40:00.320
<i>- Rydell Train Station.</i>
- Hi.

40:00.510 --> 40:02.400
When is the next train
to New York?

40:02.600 --> 40:05.890
- [booming voice] What do you
think you're doing?

40:06.090 --> 40:08.850
<i>[ethereal music]</i>

40:09.040 --> 40:10.330
<i>♪ </i>

40:10.520 --> 40:12.200
<i>- Hello?</i>
- You're stunning.

40:12.400 --> 40:13.630
I know.

40:13.830 --> 40:15.720
I am your guardian angel--

40:15.920 --> 40:20.200
the Angel of Fashion.

40:20.400 --> 40:21.380
No.

40:21.580 --> 40:23.380
I'm not talking to you.

40:23.580 --> 40:25.690
You are a figment
of my imagination.

40:25.890 --> 40:26.820
Hmm.

40:27.020 --> 40:28.560
[thunder claps]
[gasps]

40:28.760 --> 40:32.000
- I've come to tell you that
you can't run away, baby.

40:32.200 --> 40:34.350
I can, and I will.

40:34.550 --> 40:37.180
I'm finally getting
out of this dump

40:37.380 --> 40:41.050
and going to New York, where
people will appreciate me.

40:41.250 --> 40:42.620
[phone dings]

40:42.820 --> 40:46.230
[mocking laughter]

40:46.430 --> 40:49.230
[giggling]

40:49.430 --> 40:52.310
[maniacal laughter]

40:57.060 --> 40:59.940
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

41:00.140 --> 41:07.030
<i>♪ </i>

41:07.230 --> 41:09.730
♪ How interesting

41:09.930 --> 41:11.730
♪ You're sure it's your time

41:11.930 --> 41:15.130
♪ The dangerous part of youth
thinking you're in your prime ♪

41:15.330 --> 41:17.220
♪ How interesting

41:17.420 --> 41:19.260
♪ You're hitting the road

41:19.460 --> 41:22.530
♪ But let me tell you something
Crystal, darling, don't go ♪

41:22.730 --> 41:24.220
My name's not Crystal.

41:24.420 --> 41:27.660
- ♪ So fashion's meant
to change the conversation ♪

41:27.860 --> 41:31.190
- ♪ No, fashion's meant to
change my life and save it ♪

41:31.390 --> 41:33.150
♪ Slow down

41:33.350 --> 41:35.280
♪ You're blistering
my patience ♪

41:35.480 --> 41:38.240
♪ Slow down

41:38.440 --> 41:41.810
♪ Brutal honesty, girl,
that's what you need ♪

41:42.010 --> 41:45.460
♪ If you up and leave
you'll lose everything ♪

41:45.660 --> 41:47.990
♪ Stay where you can
be the rise ♪

41:48.190 --> 41:52.820
♪ Instead of the fall

41:53.020 --> 41:55.210
♪ Brutal honesty

41:55.410 --> 41:56.910
♪ Tee hee hee hee hee

41:57.110 --> 41:58.690
chorus: ♪ Brutal honesty

41:58.890 --> 42:00.260
♪ Tee hee hee hee hee

42:00.460 --> 42:01.870
♪ How interesting

42:02.070 --> 42:04.350
♪ You think I should quit

42:04.550 --> 42:07.530
♪ That's quite a proclamation
for someone who don't exist ♪

42:07.730 --> 42:09.050
Ha ha ha!

42:09.250 --> 42:12.140
♪ Oh, NYC will E-A-T you,
baby ♪

42:12.340 --> 42:13.800
So?

42:14.000 --> 42:16.490
- ♪ Sticking to your guns
requires bravery ♪

42:16.690 --> 42:18.240
♪ Hold out

42:18.430 --> 42:20.240
♪ Rydell needs your saving

42:20.440 --> 42:23.370
♪ And you still need
your friends, baby ♪

42:23.570 --> 42:27.070
♪ Brutal honesty, girl,
that's what you need ♪

42:27.270 --> 42:30.680
♪ If you up and leave,
you'll lose everything ♪

42:30.880 --> 42:33.290
♪ Stay where you
can be the rise ♪

42:33.490 --> 42:38.170
♪ Instead of the fall

42:38.370 --> 42:41.870
- ♪ Brutal honesty's
my middle name ♪

42:42.070 --> 42:45.480
♪ Told all of my friends
right to their face ♪

42:45.680 --> 42:49.350
♪ What I think of them,
and then did it again ♪

42:49.550 --> 42:52.700
♪ It ended in disaster
all the same ♪

42:52.900 --> 42:57.060
- ♪ Ugh, before I transcend
back to heaven or to hell ♪

42:57.260 --> 43:01.450
♪ I need you to be brutally
honest with yourself ♪

43:01.650 --> 43:04.540
<i>♪ </i>

43:04.740 --> 43:08.290
- ♪ Brutal honesty, damn,
that's what I need ♪

43:08.480 --> 43:11.900
♪ If I up and leave,
I'll lose everything ♪

43:12.100 --> 43:14.160
both: ♪ Stay where you can
be the rise ♪

43:14.360 --> 43:17.470
♪ Instead of the fall

43:17.670 --> 43:19.080
<i>♪ </i>

43:19.280 --> 43:21.520
♪ Brutal honesty

43:21.720 --> 43:23.170
♪ Tee hee hee hee hee

43:23.370 --> 43:25.260
chorus: ♪ Brutal honesty

43:25.460 --> 43:26.830
- ♪ Tee hee hee hee hee
- ♪ Oh

43:27.030 --> 43:28.870
both: ♪ Brutal honesty

43:29.070 --> 43:30.440
♪ Tee hee hee hee hee hee

43:30.640 --> 43:32.530
chorus: ♪ Brutal honesty

43:32.730 --> 43:34.350
♪ Tee hee hee hee hee

43:34.550 --> 43:36.570
♪ You are the fantasy

43:36.770 --> 43:39.710
♪ My darling, darling Nancy

43:39.910 --> 43:41.540
chorus: ♪ Tee hee hee hee hee

43:41.740 --> 43:43.230
Good luck to you.

43:43.430 --> 43:46.020
And don't...die.

43:46.220 --> 43:47.760
chorus: ♪ Brutal honesty

43:47.960 --> 43:49.720
♪ Tee hee hee hee hee

43:49.920 --> 43:52.680
[thunder fades]

43:52.880 --> 43:55.580
[birds chirping]

43:59.540 --> 44:01.110
Oh, no!

44:05.940 --> 44:07.600
[bell chimes]
Ahh!

44:08.770 --> 44:11.690
[sobbing]

44:19.430 --> 44:20.970
Ms. McGee?

44:21.170 --> 44:22.620
I'm sorry.

44:22.820 --> 44:24.620
I just can't do it
all alone anymore.

44:24.820 --> 44:26.280
It's too much.

44:26.480 --> 44:28.230
[blowing nose]

44:28.430 --> 44:30.670
- Maybe you could ask
for help--

44:30.870 --> 44:32.330
some adult help?

44:32.530 --> 44:33.720
[chuckles]

44:33.920 --> 44:35.850
Don't you think I've asked?

44:36.050 --> 44:39.810
Because I have,
multiple times.

44:40.010 --> 44:42.640
I've put requests through
all the official channels--

44:42.840 --> 44:45.120
Principal Nicholson,
Superintendent Fletcher,

44:45.320 --> 44:47.120
the school board.

44:47.320 --> 44:49.430
I've tried everything,
and nothing's worked.

44:49.630 --> 44:52.130
- Well, maybe it's
time to go through

44:52.330 --> 44:53.820
some unofficial channels.

45:00.210 --> 45:02.970
In a fair world,
we'd get what we need

45:03.160 --> 45:04.910
from the powers that be.

45:06.310 --> 45:09.890
In this world...

45:10.080 --> 45:12.310
sometimes we have
to color outside the lines.

45:16.400 --> 45:18.930
It's just not how I operate.

45:25.070 --> 45:26.030
Oh!

45:26.230 --> 45:27.290
Okay.

45:27.490 --> 45:29.990
[laughs] Uh, what's that for?

45:30.190 --> 45:32.950
- You just helped me
realize something.

45:33.150 --> 45:35.640
And you look like
you needed it.

45:38.080 --> 45:40.610
[lights powering up]

45:40.810 --> 45:43.350
[cheering]

45:43.550 --> 45:45.270
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

45:45.470 --> 45:47.100
Do you want another?

45:47.300 --> 45:48.780
Let's not get crazy.

45:52.440 --> 45:54.580
[birds chirping]

45:54.780 --> 45:57.580
[indistinct chatter]

46:06.150 --> 46:07.590
What are you doing in here?

46:07.790 --> 46:10.080
I've been looking
everywhere for you.

46:10.280 --> 46:11.990
- Just waiting for
everyone to clear out.

46:12.190 --> 46:14.120
I can only take so many jokes
from Rosemary and the girls

46:14.320 --> 46:15.590
about what a tramp I am.

46:18.380 --> 46:21.090
I just came to say goodbye,

46:21.290 --> 46:23.090
and to give you this--

46:23.290 --> 46:25.570
as a friend.

46:25.770 --> 46:27.610
Thank you for
running my campaign.

46:29.040 --> 46:32.360
And thanks.

46:32.560 --> 46:34.790
Thanks for being my first.

46:38.090 --> 46:40.670
- Funny, you're the only
friend I have left at Rydell,

46:40.870 --> 46:43.200
and you are leaving.

46:43.400 --> 46:47.160
- Trust me, if there were
any way to avoid it, I would.

46:47.360 --> 46:50.160
<i>[somber music]</i>

46:50.360 --> 46:55.690
<i>♪ </i>

46:55.890 --> 46:58.430
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

46:58.630 --> 46:59.600
<i>♪ </i>

46:59.800 --> 47:00.650
You're still here!

47:00.850 --> 47:02.350
Good.

47:02.540 --> 47:04.170
Oh, and Nancy too.

47:04.370 --> 47:05.520
Where's Olivia?

47:05.720 --> 47:07.790
Nancy, what happened to you?

47:07.990 --> 47:09.090
- I know I said some
horrible things,

47:09.290 --> 47:10.530
but I take them all back.

47:10.730 --> 47:12.000
None of it was true.

47:14.740 --> 47:18.130
- Actually, you were
kind of right about me.

47:19.740 --> 47:22.970
The Pink Ladies changed me
for the better.

47:23.170 --> 47:24.500
Yeah.

47:24.700 --> 47:27.020
You were right about me
not being a T-Bird too.

47:27.220 --> 47:29.720
This isn't the jacket
I want to be wearing.

47:29.920 --> 47:31.240
- I thought you said
it was crazy,

47:31.440 --> 47:34.200
you being a Pink Lady.

47:34.400 --> 47:37.950
- The Boston Red Sox
are neither red, nor socks,

47:38.150 --> 47:40.600
but they're still a team.

47:40.800 --> 47:43.210
- Oh, well, in that case, maybe
I don't need to apologize.

47:43.410 --> 47:44.520
No, you definitely do.

47:44.720 --> 47:46.520
- Yeah, you were
way out of line.

47:46.720 --> 47:48.960
I'm sorry.

47:49.160 --> 47:50.960
Olivia was right.

47:51.160 --> 47:54.310
I am the one who needs
the Pink Ladies.

47:54.510 --> 47:56.230
You all are always
falling in and out of love

47:56.420 --> 48:00.660
with Richie and Buddy
and Mr. Daniels and Shy Guy.

48:00.860 --> 48:04.890
And--and sometimes I feel
like what's going on with me

48:05.090 --> 48:07.450
isn't as important as all
the drama in your lives.

48:07.650 --> 48:11.840
But I've realized
I have a love story too.

48:13.360 --> 48:15.720
I'm in love with...

48:15.920 --> 48:17.020
us.

48:18.930 --> 48:20.680
And I know that's weird.

48:20.880 --> 48:22.380
I know that's not
the way you're supposed

48:22.580 --> 48:23.510
to feel about your friends.

48:23.710 --> 48:26.780
But I don't care.

48:26.980 --> 48:28.470
I love us.

48:32.950 --> 48:34.520
I love us too.

48:34.720 --> 48:36.610
Me too.

48:36.810 --> 48:38.260
- I miss us.
- Oh!

48:42.780 --> 48:45.670
- FYI, this is
a one-time thing.

48:45.870 --> 48:47.890
Tell anyone of my
vulnerable nature

48:48.090 --> 48:49.920
and I will deny it
till the day I die.

48:52.360 --> 48:54.330
Let's go find Olivia.

48:54.530 --> 48:55.760
She's not with you?

48:55.960 --> 48:56.720
I've been looking for her.

48:56.920 --> 48:58.160
She's probably at home.

48:58.360 --> 49:00.720
- We have to talk to her,
and Richie too.

49:00.920 --> 49:03.550
We're going to find a way
to keep him here at Rydell.

49:03.750 --> 49:05.900
And since the adults
won't help,

49:06.100 --> 49:08.770
We'll just have
to do it our own way.

49:10.160 --> 49:11.560
I'll drive.

49:11.760 --> 49:14.220
<i>[uplifting music]</i>

49:14.420 --> 49:16.220
<i>♪ </i>

49:16.420 --> 49:17.390
Hey.

49:17.590 --> 49:18.730
I--

49:22.170 --> 49:28.140
<i>♪ </i>

49:28.340 --> 49:30.230
<i>chorus: ♪ Brutal honesty </i>

49:30.430 --> 49:32.060
<i>♪ Tee hee hee hee hee </i>

49:32.260 --> 49:33.980
[whistling]

49:34.170 --> 49:36.020
Oh. Look who's still here.

49:36.220 --> 49:38.590
Have yourself a lovely
evening, Miss McGee.

49:38.790 --> 49:39.800
No.

49:41.450 --> 49:43.940
You listen to me, buster.

49:44.140 --> 49:46.120
I'll do anything
for this school.

49:46.320 --> 49:47.550
But I'm only one woman.

49:47.750 --> 49:48.770
I can't do it alone.

49:48.970 --> 49:50.380
[sighs]

49:50.580 --> 49:51.860
If you're asking me to
take on some of your duties--

49:52.060 --> 49:53.390
Please! You?

49:53.590 --> 49:54.990
You wouldn't last two seconds.

49:57.380 --> 50:01.730
Look, if it's not
too much trouble...

50:03.470 --> 50:06.700
I think it might be nice--

50:06.900 --> 50:08.440
I would--I would like a--

50:11.090 --> 50:14.230
I demand an assistant,

50:14.430 --> 50:15.970
or I quit!

50:16.170 --> 50:19.060
Good night to you.

50:19.260 --> 50:22.060
[whistling]

50:25.060 --> 50:27.550
What's gotten into her?

50:27.750 --> 50:31.290
<i>- ♪ If it's good,</i>
<i>then I want it ♪</i>

50:31.490 --> 50:36.690
<i>♪ If it's bad,</i>
<i>I don't need it ♪</i>

50:36.890 --> 50:41.870
<i>♪ If it's good,</i>
<i>then I crave it ♪</i>

50:42.070 --> 50:47.000
<i>♪ If it's bad, baby,</i>
<i>we'll save it ♪</i>

50:47.200 --> 50:50.270
<i>♪ My man, they told me</i>
<i>long ago ♪</i>

50:50.470 --> 50:51.790
What are you doing here?

50:51.990 --> 50:53.100
- We have to tell
you something.

50:53.300 --> 50:54.140
We love you, and I take
back everything that I--

50:54.340 --> 50:55.400
Shh!

51:03.320 --> 51:05.200
What is he doing here?

51:05.400 --> 51:07.020
- Asking for my
parents' blessing.

51:10.150 --> 51:11.450
We're getting married.

51:14.020 --> 51:15.210
Okay.

51:15.410 --> 51:16.430
Where's Richie?

51:16.620 --> 51:18.070
There's no way he's for this.

51:19.640 --> 51:21.030
I thought you knew.

51:25.340 --> 51:26.520
[sighs]

51:26.720 --> 51:29.610
My parents put him
on a bus this afternoon.

51:29.810 --> 51:31.090
He's gone, Jane.

51:31.290 --> 51:34.050
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

51:34.250 --> 51:40.830
<i>♪ </i>

51:42.010 --> 51:43.530
Olivia!

51:47.750 --> 51:49.720
I think you should leave.

51:49.920 --> 51:55.070
<i>♪ </i>

51:55.270 --> 51:56.640
There she is.

51:56.840 --> 51:58.080
<i>Felicidades.</i>

51:58.280 --> 51:59.150
Mm.

52:07.030 --> 52:12.920
<i>♪ </i>

52:13.120 --> 52:15.910
[indistinct speech]

52:25.010 --> 52:26.660
- I think this
belongs with you.

52:34.060 --> 52:36.150
[sniffling]

52:37.500 --> 52:40.550
- What are we
supposed to do now?

52:40.750 --> 52:43.030
- We were thinking about that,
and...

52:43.230 --> 52:45.730
We have no clue.

52:45.930 --> 52:48.420
But we know one thing.

52:50.680 --> 52:53.260
You're Jane Facciano.

52:53.460 --> 52:55.430
- Jane Facciano
never gives up.

52:57.470 --> 52:59.790
<i>[Andy Russell's "What</i>
<i>a Diff'rence a Day Made"]</i>

52:59.990 --> 53:06.060
<i>- ♪ What a difference</i>
<i>a day made ♪</i>

53:06.260 --> 53:11.320
<i>♪ 24 little hours </i>

53:11.520 --> 53:15.190
<i>♪ Brought the sun</i>
<i>and the flowers ♪</i>
